[
    {
        "content": "<p>I am trying add the fun_prop attribute to the following lemma:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">@[</span><span class=\"n\">fun_prop</span><span class=\"kd\">]</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">lemma</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">measurable_entry</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Ω</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Matrix</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Fin</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Fin</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hX</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Measurable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Fin</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Fin</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Measurable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ω</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↦</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ω</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">intros</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">j</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">fun_prop</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>(the <code>MeasurableSpace</code> structure on <code>Matrix (Fin m) (Fin n) α</code> is the product one where <code>α</code> is a <code>MeasurableSpace</code>). However, I get an error <code>Not a valid `fun_prop` theorem!</code>.  I believe it has to do with the ∀ (i : Fin m) (j : Fin n) part (correct me if I'm wrong please). What's the correct way to state this and still have a lemma with the fun_prop attribute that states that the entries are measurable functions?</p>",
